docs.text: wild wild west
docs.label: negative

docs.text: a better name for this movie might've been " wild wild waste " .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: warner bros . , in an attempt to get their own men in black style of movie , had managed to lasso in some big names ( actor will smith and director barry sonnenfeld , the duo behind mib's success ) in order to get their own fourth of july blockbuster , a contemporary big-screen update to the classic western/sci-fi series the wild wild west starring robert conrad .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but somehow , they ran into a problem along the way .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: they were so busy trying to fill specific roles that they forgot one in general that would've made all the difference- a story writer .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: wild wild west's story and script was compiled by six different people , rather than just the one who put the brilliant touches on men in black , ed solomon .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: if warner bros . had gotten him , the movie would've possibly been five times better than what it is .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: heck , ten times .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: as is , however , the story and screenplay is a mess , filled with dead laughs , enough racist and sex jokes to make even will cringe as he's performing them , and a complete lack of chemistry that made the tv show work so well .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: here's the story : us army member james west ( will smith ) teams up with creative genius artemus gordon ( kevin kline ) to take on a ruthless villain by the name of arliss loveless ( kenneth branagh ) , whose lower half was blown off during the civil war , leaving him to roll around in a steam-controlled wheelchair .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: they catch onto a plot of his involving a superweapon that can basically be considered an 80-foot tarantula ( although it looks bigger than that ) , hellbent on destroying anything in its path .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: as i said , the way the script unfolds is a complete mess .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but the acting doesn't help either .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: kevin kline is miserable as gordon , failing to display even a smidgeon of care as he did in the 1985 western silverado .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: smith seems to be having a better time as west , although he's not nearly as charming as he was in mib .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: branagh goes excessively over the top as the villain , perhaps to the point where we can't even stand to look at him or his strange beard .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and salma hayek is along for the ride to search for her missing father , but mostly she exists just for sexual attention .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: her acting is barely passable , but what a " breath of fresh ass " .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: director barry sonnenfeld isn't of great help either .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: even though he shows some good creativity at some points , his overall urgency for directing is lost .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it's as if he feels he's directing a tv movie , a big no-no when you're helming what's supposed to be a big-screen hit .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: last but not least , there are huge gaps of logic that are just plain unacceptable .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: at one point , smith defies gravity when first boarding kline's train .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he jumps on the back , gets launched straight up in the air , and somehow manages to land three cars ahead on the train- while it's still in motion !
docs.label: negative

docs.text: also , he seems to be strangely comfortable talking about racism in front of a lynch mob , particularly considering the fact that his family was killed by the likes of such folks .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: last but not least , why is he still making kissing faces when he knows he's not kissing a woman as he's looking through a peephole at the enemy ? !
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the only saving grace for wild wild west come mostly in the form of special effects .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the huge mechanical spider is a technical marvel , very authentic looking and considerable to the creativity of the show .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there's also a good sequence involving metal magnet neckbraces and spinning saw blades , but , again , a logic question comes into play regarding their polarity .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i would say sit back and have a good time with wild wild west , but it really isn't possible .
